caption: Always a great brunch! The mimosas are replaced before you've finished the one you have, never have to wait. The staff is wonderful- kind, generous and professional. The food is really good and comes in large portions- much better value for money than any other brunch place I've been in Chicago.

Stumbled across here by accident! Felt welcome from the very moment I walked in. Staff was warm, friendly, and customer service was some of the best I’ve seen in a longtime. Even though our reservations got screwed up somehow ,they figured out a way to seat us with no issues. Atmosphere was great, it was the Sunday bottomless mimosas so I expected the high energy. Food was yummy can’t wait to try dinner here

I have never had a bad experience here or bad food. We went in for Valentine’s dinner. Being so busy after just opening back up after not being able to have dine in for a long time they were busy. But things were running well. Unfortunately our dishes were undercooked or still frozen. We mentioned to the waiter we just wanted to pay for our drinks and we were just going to head out. Again, they were busy and we didn’t want to cause fuss. The owner came out and told us we weren’t going anywhere. He prepared us two pasta dishes off the menu himself. Had more drinks brought out to us and after served us champagne and tiramisu. We asked for none of that but we’re SO extremely grateful. Our night wouldn’t have been ruined if we had to eat at home. I work in the service industry. I know how it was to open back up after being closed for months. Being treated with such kindness and care was one of the greatest dining experiences we both have had. I love this place and will always go here and recommend it to anyone.
Eggs Benedict are to DIE for. Staff was very friendly. Will definitely return!
Great food! Great service. It always good for lunchtime.

Usually love this place, we ordered take out and both of our meals were very sub par. My pasta was very dry and had maybe half the sauce that has always been on the same dish, hers they completely changed the recipe for the sauce and took out the main meat that they use in it. When I called about it they said they had changed it on their menu but when I checked on their website guess what still says the old recipe so not only was it not right the person answering the phone straight up lied to me about it. Definitely changed our mind about getting take out from what use to be our favorite spot.

Also the servers look as if they are happy to be there which is always a plus. Of course it wouldn't be a good review if I were to skip out on the food. They know traditional Italian food and do it well. Highly recommend any of their dishes (you can't go wrong), it all depends on what you're in the mood for that night.

We had a reservation, otherwise wouldn’t have been able to be seated within a reasonable time.  The food was amazing, with the majority of the table getting pasta dishes. Our mimosas weren’t the best I’ve ever had, but nothing to complain about.  The only bit that was really annoying was how loudly they played the music. Well where do I start? I don't know what it was about last night, but we had a very interesting experience at Angelina. We went there because I remembers that I really enjoyed one dinner with a friend a couple of years ago. Unfortunately, this time it was a completely different experience! 1. Dishwashers kept slamming the dishes in the kitchen, they were super loud! One patron went in to ask them to be more gentle with the dishes, and it still didn't help. 2) we ordered mussels, they smelled like.. barn? pee? I always order mussels whenever they are on the menu, and something was wrong with these ones. A couple at the table next to ours also had mussels, and they didn't complain though (trying to be objective.) 3) Burrata - it's not the creamy kind that I expected, but a regular mozzarella from Jewel. 4) Salmon Pasta - the pasta was very pale, with a blah texture, the sauce was watery and left sour aftertaste, salmon was terribly overcooked and dry. 5) duck.. they didn't trim excess fat as they should have, the dish lacked flavor. My fiance had salmon as his main course, and it was, once again, dry. The place was half-empty, and still they were very slow with everything. We got there at 7, and we only got to eat at 8 (by that time we  only had caprese, and we had to send the mussels back.) 6) One of the busboys was snacking while cleaning the tables - literally walking with a plate of food, and chewing. He didn't seem to care about his job at all. The whole experience was so amusing and ridiculous, that we decided not to cancel our order after the mussels fiasco, but hope for the best and see what else was going to go wrong. We were barely able to hold down laughter when they brought pasta and main plates. It was just ridiculous! The food was SO plain, we rated it as "one step above cafeteria food." We decided to leave and finish the night at our beloved Mia Francesca a few blocks away. We had the real burrata there, and had their delicious cheesecake and chocolate chip cookie with cinnamon gelato. One good thing about Angelina (well, two!) - the waiter, the bartender and the water busboy were very good. I've never written a review like this before, but this time I felt like I absolutely had to. I truly hope that you have a better experience when you go there.

Angelina's is one of my favorite spots in Chicago. They always greet a solo traveler as a friend and the food is perfect.
This place is cash only and is super loud.
Cozy Italian food place. Great food and good prices. Definitely a great place to visit for a dates night or small groups of people.

saturday morning was super busy but the atmosphere was still great; it's very loud! but that's bound to happen when you're served all-you-can-drink mimosas. service was a little slow but once people started leaving we were treated like queens. food was EXCELLENT!
Great spot for brunch!! Drinks are refilled without question and a fun friend atmosphere overall! Highly recommend!
Perfect atmosphere, food and location.   Great service, friendly staff.  The food is amazing!
My partner and I had a great meal here with our 4 year old. Very cute, quaint and cozy place with excellent food and friendly attentive staff. We loved it.
Great food and service.
The food used to be better. And they lost my hat 1 day after calling to tell me they had found it and were holding it for me.
Great spot. Great brunch deal. I've been there twice and I havent been disappointed, but I think this just is a really good local brunch spot if you live in the area
Hands down the BEST Italian restaurant that I can Honestly call my second home! Impeccable menu and staff ....the combination of the two makes one feel right back home in Italy! La Dolce Vita!
The food was fine, huge portions.
Nice atmosphere. Wonderful aromas when you walk in. I had a nice Caesar salad. I ordered the wild mushroom fettuccine  and it was good, but every couple of bites I got grit!
Amazing!!
Great food, intimate setting
GREAT Italian food, service & ambience.  Warm bread w olive oil. Great wine selection too.  Sunday brunch is great time to go w friends & see other friends.
I've been here for brunch and dinner and have been floored by how delicious everything is! So cozy and romantic too!
Love this neighbor restaurant. Will customize any menu item!
Charming, nothing beats the bottomless mimosa brunch on Sat-Sun. Get there early.

I was here for New Year. All that I ate was very good. The place is very cozy with candles, it creates a romantic place. Service is little bit long and not very organized. Plates are very big, that is a good thing but they should do regular size of plates and decrease a little bit prices.
Y'all Angelina's is dopeee must go
Had a good brunch.
The food here is absolutely amazing. Everything is good. Every. Thing.
Great food, decent prices.
Great brunch special! $23 for meal and unlimited minosas
Champagne Brunch is A++. $23 for endless mimosas and the food is great and you're not shorted on the serving.

I went here for brunch. Wouldn't seat us without our whole party, which is fair. There was plenty of seating available, but I really do understand that policy. What I do not understand is why we were directed to stand in the middle of everything while we waited rather than truly off to the side. The host put us right in the path of the servers. It was too hot, too cramped, and too loud. Music was ridiculous - I love EDM and all that stuff, but not blasting at brunch. Coffee refills were far and few between, which was a blessing and a curse since the coffee was not very good, but I was quite tired. Food was fine but the preparation of the lox plate, while aesthetically pleasing, was impractical for actually eating the food. Onions cut up too finely. Cherry tomatoes rolling all over the place. Like seriously what am I supposed to do with that? I don't wanna chase down my food on my own plate! Won't be returning. The friends I went with had a much better time than I did. Seems like an OK place, but not good for the 25 going on 65 crowd.

If you are a person who doesn't like having to yell over the ambient noise, this place is great. But the positives don't stop there: atmosphere, food, service, all fantastic. A wonderfully intimate authentically Italian ristorante. Would come back here in a flash.
Great food and friendly atmosphere...

Been coming here for years. Never disappointed. Consistently good. No it isn't Spiaggia, but they seem to put a bit of love in everything they do. Friendly and effective service. Pastas, meats, seafood...never have I felt anything but satisfied. To me it's the definition of a quality neighborhood restaurant.  The naysayers, in this case, are wrong.

Incredible food here, our whole table loved their meal, my pasta dish was fantastic and a friend claimed to have the best steak he'd ever had here.  The staff were very friendly and managed to fit us in immediately without a booking. Great atmosphere though perhaps a little too hot inside.
Nice place for Sunday brunch, however as a lover of Bloody Mary's I was very disappointed. The garnishing was inconsistent and they need to boost up the horseradish.
Good brunch though rather noisy with conversation clashing with the volume of the music.
Great food and service
Not bad at all. Not overly noisy....

Horrible server! I have never experienced such rude service. I over heard him say "get the f*** out of here". We weren't even there that long, and 60% of the time we were waiting for our food. Never come back to that place.
The bread was great but that was unfortunately the best part of the meal. Our waiter seemed to forget about us. The food came out cold and we never received the water refill I asked for.

Well, what can I say about this little gem? It is such a great dimly dimly-lit environment for incredibly authentic Italian food. Perfect for dates, groups, the family, or just yourself. The service is terrific and you always feel welcome when you are greeted not by a host, but the owner himself (Hint: He always wears a white crew). He asks where you'd like to sit and then the feast begins. I've been here many times and I really enjoy their Eggplant Parmesan and any pasta or seafood. Seriously. Try the desserts with with a cup of espresso too!
The bottomless mimosa breakfast is a good deal and the restaurant usually isn't that packed. The servers are attentive and the decor is nice.
We came for a late dinner and it was fantastic service. We had the meatballs and pasta pomidoro. The food and wine was delicious. We will definitely come here again!

rather disappointing. risotto was a joke - a HUGE pile of pre-cooked rice mixed with some cheese and asparagus. the squash ravioli was barely passable. the plating is just sad. the wine list is made up of supermarket wines. the "sorbetto" tasted store bought as well. the service was decent. i don't understand its popularity. definitely not the kind of neighborhood place you can be proud of...
Great customer service.The food was great as well. Really friendly!
(Translated by Google) Rich food and excellent service  (Original) Rica comida y excelente atención
My "Go To" place for Sunday brunch!  Love the atmosphere and love the food!
I've been here several times and have always had amazing service, wine and FOOD!!! The portions are huge and always delicious and the desserts are amazing. The brunch is next on my list to check out.
Good mimosas. Beefy Bloody Marys. Good tunes and definitely the place where the gossip flows.

Such a great neighborhood gem! Warm bread, good wine, and food that tastes straight out of Italy.  It is shocking how close this is to Wrigley with no traces of Wrigley within.  Don't pass up the bruschetta!

Cozy and charming atmosphere with very friendly wait staff. Makes for a good date night spot as you can actually hear the person you're dining with. I had the gnocchi which was light, fluffy, and very tasty.

I simply LOVE coming to this intimate Italian place to MIMOSAS!!! I always have a great time here with my friends. Their food is really good, their smoked salmon eggs benedicts are my favorite. Their mimosa deal is wonderful on weekends. The many times I've been in this restaurant, the staff is really, really nice. For sure, one of my favorites places in Lakeview.

The food was a mixed bag. The split pea soup was smokey and dynamite, the ricotta gnocchi were light and airy and really wonderful little pillows, but sadly I found their basic marinara ot be a little flavorless, it was sweet and red but it didn't really have any depth. We did finish with a chocolate bread pudding that was a bit sweet but was very very good.  The ambience of this place however, is excellent. It feels like a little quaint place in the west village, not a lot of space , but you don't feel like you're on top of each other, it just feels cozy. Sound volume is very low, it's a nice place for a date because you can really hear your dining partner and don't have to yell over the din around you.  The staff was attentive and excellent.

Angelina became a tradition among my friends and I. Every time we have somebody leaving Chicago for good, we go over there on Saturdays to celebrate the great friendship we had together! Their brunch is simply amazing. I've ordered their stuffed croissant and my friends ordered the eggs benedict, both amazing dishes. And don't forget to choose the Mimosas Brunch on Satusrday! For only $21 you get unlimited mimosas and a dish of your choice.

Their brunch is the best! Unlimited mimosas and any item on the menu all for $21! It's a wonderful thing. Their dinner is also amazing. I've tried their pasta, braised beef short ribs, and the duck, all of which were top notch. The only …

Angelina is one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago. It reminds me of truly Italian fare I had when in Italy. I love that you can find dishes with fresh mozzarella and basil. The restaurant itself is so cute, quaint and romantic. I love this restaurant for date night!

A great italian place in lakeview! The staff here are super friendly and attentive. I am a local so after coming here a few times, some of the waiters remembers me! (They are also quite good looking) The pasta is delicious and fresh. The best is their dessert, the bread pudding. You can't leave without trying this!
cool storefront restaurant.  attentive service, excellent food.  Fun to experience.  Reasonable prices.
Hands down, best brunch in Lakeview!
Brunch is amazing.  Food is delicious and the staff are so personable. The food is so fresh and made from scratch.  I love coming to Angelina any day!
First time I went was on my birthday.  I ate one of the seafood dishes and it was very good!  Parking is accessible on the weekends.  The prices are reasonable for pretty good quality Italian food.
Best brunch in Chicago!!!  the entrees are pretty great, but the bottomless mimosas complete the package.
This is a wonderful place to go to for a Saturday or Sunday brunch - especially with a large group.  They have a deal for $21 you get an entree and bottomless mimosas.
very cozy and friendly
Great Bloody Mary's!
If you want the real Italian experience stop in this cossy and local places, the food and wines are great. The pasta will never taste the same.

This restaurant is so good! The food for dinner is exquisite, and the brunch vibe is hoppin'. On top of that, the wait staff serves as some serious eye candy for those of us that enjoy a good lookin man. Romantic ambiance for a date.
I've been here for both dinner and Sunday brunch.  The atmosphere is lively and the food is delicious.  Make sure you bring your green on Sundays as brunch is cash only, but the mimosas flow freely!

An adorable, cute, hidden little taste of Italy. The food is very delicious - their pastas are top notch and their soup is delicious. The waiters are very nice and helpful. The atmosphere can be romantic or a great place to dine with friends.

They double charged my credit card and refused to refund any of the money. They took our reservation for a certain number and could not seat us all, so we ended up having to send our guests away. Ridiculous in size, don't advertise that you can do parties when your entire establishment is less than 100 square feet. Over priced for the food and wine. Shabby and cheap decor.

This place is known for the fun brunch place that started it all. Recently I have been going to dinner here more than brunch. I really enjoy, the risoto and pasta fucili. The bread pudding is amazing and will keep you coming back for more. The facilities are very cramped but cozy. If you are clausterphobic, don't come here and it's a bit overwhelming but the food is good.

When I first moved to the city, I lived across the street from this place and immediately fell in love with it's authentic charm. They have legitimate Italian food and a great wine selection- the smell of garlic, tomato, and mushroom hits you when you walk in. They also offer a great and affordable brunch on Sundays- amazing eggs florentine! You cannot go wrong with the chicken marsala or lasagna- solid Italian classics.
Lunch time
Best Chicago brunch. $10 entree with $10 limitless mimosas, bellinis or kir royales. Arrive early.
One of my go-to places for Italian food.  Great waiters.  I understand why there are RAVES for the brunch.  I love it for dinner.
Best spot in Chicago for Gay brunch! All you can drink mimosas and fun time shenanigans
